place_name: Knowledge Perk Coffee Company | Fort Mill

details.description:
Come relax in our beautiful café with indoor and outdoor seating. We offer freshly roasted coffee, cold brew, full range of expert espresso beverages, and a variety of sweet and savory pastries and bagel creations.

Thursday-Friday from 4:00pm-9:30pm, and Saturday from 6:00pm-9:30pm, we turn into Knowledge Perk "After Hours," serving coffee, original cocktails, beer, and wine.

We are a coffee roaster and beans are available onsite or via our website for retail purchase. We have immersive, engaging programs and events for our community to grow in their knowledge and enjoyment of coffee. Give us a call or visit our website for more information. Better yet, drop by to see us in person!

reviews_data.review_text: Always enjoy to try new coffee shop locations and this time my choice fell on this one since we were visiting the area. We ordered salmon bagel and two lattes. Salmon bagel had about 1% of salmon in it, 85% cream cheese and 14% was massive chunks of purple onions mix with cream cheese. I had a bad heartburn after it. I did ask not to put it there but they said it’s all pre made mix. Coffee tasted more like water and coffee than a coffee and milk. Overall 25$ down the drain. Won’t be coming back.

Our first time in the Fort Mill location and we were very disappointed. The atmosphere wasn't there for us like the one in Rock Hill. We didn't stay long because it was freezing in there. No wonder there was hardly anybody in there on a Friday night. They have it so cold that nobody wants to stay. A coffee shop is supposed to be cozy and relaxing, not feel like a freezer. Probably won't be back.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Dear Debbie,
We appreciate all feedback, even when it’s tough to hear. It’s unfortunate that your experience at our Fort Mill location didn’t meet your expectations, especially since you seemed to enjoy our Rock Hill shop. While we strive to create a comfortable atmosphere for all guests, we also recognize that temperature preferences can vary widely. Our team is always happy to adjust when concerns are brought to our attention during a visit. I’m very confident our team would’ve been very happy to adjust temperatures if requested. It was also 20° outside, and so we understand a hot cup of coffee would certainly add to the warmness as our heaters were likely working overtime. 

That said, we’ve noticed that your reviews tend to lean toward the negative, which makes us wonder if the issue is less about our coffee shop and more about your approach to customer experiences. We take great pride in what we do, and while we may not be the right fit for everyone, we are confident in the warm and welcoming environment we provide to thousands of happy guests. I’m not sure a one star review in this case is extremely warranted, nor is it fair to us as a small business when we do a phenomenal job in so many other areas on a very consistent basis. 

If you’d like to give us another try, we’d love the opportunity to change your mind. If not, we sincerely hope you find a coffee shop that better aligns with your preferences and temperature.

Wishing you all the best,
Ryan.

reviews_data.review_text:
I visit occasionally to catch up with a friend. We like their coffee and it's a relatively quiet place. You get a lot of street traffic noise if you sit outside. Inside is better obviously, to avoid that.

No matter what coffee you get they are usually right on the money. Also they roast their own beans at their Rock Hill location.

They have a limited amount of snacks in display case by the register and only occasionally have I ever see something that might be gluten free. So if that's you thing plan on the possibility of not having something to eat.

Come relax in our beautiful café with indoor and outdoor seating. We offer freshly roasted coffee, cold brew, full range of expert espresso beverages, and a variety of sweet and savory pastries and bagel creations.

Dear Debbie,
We appreciate all feedback, even when it’s tough to hear. It’s unfortunate that your experience at our Fort Mill location didn’t meet your expectations, especially since you seemed to enjoy our Rock Hill shop. While we strive to create a comfortable atmosphere for all guests, we also recognize that temperature preferences can vary widely. Our team is always happy to adjust when concerns are brought to our attention during a visit. I’m very confident our team would’ve been very happy to adjust temperatures if requested. It was also 20° outside, and so we understand a hot cup of coffee would certainly add to the warmness as our heaters were likely working overtime.

We take great pride in what we do, and while we may not be the right fit for everyone, we are confident in the warm and welcoming environment we provide to thousands of happy guests. Ryan.
